Jordan Bell (born January 7, 1995) is an American professional basketball player for the Golden State Warriors of the National Basketball Association. He played college basketball for the Oregon Ducks.

  • 1 High school and college career
  • 2 Professional career
  • 3 References
  • 4 External links

High school and college career[edit]

Bell attended Long Beach Polytechnic High School in Long Beach, California.[1] He committed to the University of Oregon to play college basketball.[2]

As a freshman at Oregon, Bell averaged 5.1 points, 6.1 rebounds and 2.7 blocks per game.[3] His 94 blocks were a school record for a season.[4] As a sophomore, he averaged 7.0 points, 5.4 rebounds and 1.8 blocks per game.[5] As a junior, Bell averaged 10.9 points, 8.8 rebounds and 2.3 blocks per game and helped lead Oregon to the Final Four.[6][7]

Professional career[edit]

On April 18, 2017, Bell declared for the 2017 NBA draft,[8] and was picked with the 38th pick by the Chicago Bulls and later traded to the Golden State Warriors.[9] Despite his 6'8" listing, Jordan measured at only 6'7" at the NBA Pre-Draft Combine[10]
